book brings their compelling story to the forefront, exploring their myriad forms and how their worship played out in the context of Roman religion's daily practice. Exploring the place of the manes in Roman society, Charles King delves into Roman beliefs about their powers to sustain life and bring death to individuals or armies, examines the rituals the Romans performed to honor them, and reclaims the vital role the manes played in the ancient Roman afterlife.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCultszRome. 0aDeadxReligious aspects. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonieszRome. 0aGods, Roman. 0aHousehold shrineszRome. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32020440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477320211423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781477320211.jpg  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK